\section* {INTRODUCTION} 
\par Climate change is affecting organisms by altering conditions such as temperature and soil moisture around the world \citep{parmesan2006,chen2011}. Some of the most widespread biological responses to climate change are shifts in phenology, the timing of recurring biological events, which have shifted 2.3-5.1 days per decade \citep{parmesan2006,poloczanska2013,root2003}. Shifts in plant phenology are the most widely documented, with spring phenology (budburst, leafout, and flowering) occurring earlier in recent years \citep{wolkovich2012}, and senescence occurring later \citep{taylor2008,delpierre2009}. 
